metadata.name: Rhythms #20
metadata.description:
"Routines, patterns, cadence.
Events, turns, chaos.
Predictable lives,
split-second dramas."

This project is inspired by the delicate balance between daily habits and life-turning points.
There's structure in the flow. There's awe in the silence.

"Rhythms" invites you to reflect on the beautiful complexity that fills our vital experience, on the millions of tiny details that bring texture to our journey causing balance or disruption.

-

Key Features:
- 12 color palettes: Determines colors used on the artwork
- 3 Orientation modes (square, portrait, landscape): Portrait and landscape are rare
- 6 Alignment Types: Determines lines' distribution pattern

Secondary features provide additional variation.

Enter live mode and press "s" to download high resolution image ( 5940x5940 px ).

-

50% of secondary market royalties go to minters.
Coded in p5js, with love.

metadata.name: (Anti)thesis #22
metadata.description:
This is my first fxhash work. It is a generative, deterministic, object-oriented algorithm written entirely in p5.js. With the exception of two very rare background colours, the colour palettes are not pre-selected but entirely generated using your transaction hash.

The algorithm plays on the concept of Antithesis (/ænˈtɪθəsɪs/ - direct contrast; opposition) by using opposing forces to generate tension (and occasional calm) between forms on the page and the spaces in between. Inspiration was also drawn from works and advice from the great Daniel Catt (@revdancatt).

I hope you like it. Thanks for your support.
tallzy

metadata.name: Deconstructions #119
metadata.description:
Deconstructions is a further experiment with blending 3 colors and 3 different textures to create structural/abstract compositions. It's a search for beauty within asymmetrical/unsynchronized forms and disharmonic structures.


Probabilities;

- 18 compositions with variations.

- 2 background colors.

- 3 different particle starting placements.

- 21 different base color palettes. (1 monochrome) 

- 2 different alpha types; tangential & randomized.

- Different edges.

- Several starting positions and styles (wavy or straight).

Additional animation features with different shapes, angles, direction and style.


In live mode, press ‘s’ to save as .png (1500x2000 px)

It can take up to a minute to render or longer in low-performance computers. Enjoy the process!


Made with p5.js

Ilgın İçözü, May 2022
@distcollective

metadata.name: Paper Planes #94
metadata.description:
The joys of childhood are too easily forgotten. Paper Planes is a generative art collection celebrating the joy and magic of origami: from the simplest materials spring delightful forms brimming with ingenuity.

In homage to the handicraft of paper folding, we developed a collection of four pens each with a unique hand-drawn feel: Ink, Pencil, Gel and Dip. They ensure each of our ten origami birds are sketched with subtle imperfections.

Many of the birds are folded from patterned paper based on three traditional Japanese patterns: Seigaiha, Kōjitsunagi and Shippō. Other birds are crafted from block coloured paper which provides pop and contrast whilst sometimes birds match their background, accentuating the hand-drawn strokes that sketched them.

A range of layouts bring each mint to life. Birds can flock and fly across the page. They can be confined to a regimented grid or they can escape and embrace the chaos of the currents. Contrasting frames and borders highlight different colours within each of the 15 handcrafted palettes.

If you're feeling mischievous you can press 'C' in live view to ruffle some feathers…

https://www.phaust.art/paper-planes

----------

In live view, press 'S' to save a high resolution download or add '&size=#' to the end of the URL to render at a custom height.

Original artwork by Phaust. Spring 2022. London / Brighton. Made with p5js.

metadata.name: Consequence Broadcast [Speed Run] #93
metadata.description:
a.k.a. Reaction Diffusion. The canvas is a grid of cells, each containing some amount of A and some amount of B. Every step, A and B react with each other and diffuse into neighbouring cells. The amounts of diffusion and reaction have different settings, which can vary across the canvas or over time. Then, cool things happen with colours. 

This is an experimental project, created as part of a Speed Run over ~37 hours in one weekend (I did also sleep and eat in that time. I even went for a walk. Go me). 
- It requires WEBGL2 and is GPU intensive. 
- There may be slight discrepancies in the patterns on different devices, due to rounding. 

Big thanks to everyone who followed along/offered advice and especially to Piter Pasma who helped me out with the noise dithering code that took everything to the next dimension.

Press P to pause.
Press 1-5 to alter speed.

metadata.name: Inertia #592
metadata.description:
This project will be reserved and free for 48 hours, for all the holders of any of my projects!

The amount of reserves for each user will be equal to the amount of all the token held at 13:00 CEST [UTC+2] (May 23)
(example: user holds 3 "Figment" and 2 "ACCUMULATOR", will be able to mint "Inertia" 5 times)

48h from now I will update the reserves list and burn the remaining tokens

WARINING: The reserves will expire 48h after the drop! And a price for the unlocked mintables will be set (unreserved mints will not be free).

---

"Inertia is a property of matter by which it continues in its existing state of rest or uniform motion in a straight line, unless that state is changed by an external force."

Particles are blasted from 2 to 4 sides of the canvas, each particle has its own mass and it has to traverse a friction-field, once it loses its momentum completely it stops and leaves a trace, adding or subtracting light from the canvas.

The friction-field has 18 possible mutation kinds.
Mutations are high-friction zones of various shapes.

Made just with JS on a canvas
right-click to save

metadata.name: Metropolis IX #88
metadata.description:
We divide spaces into smaller spaces which we conquer and live in our solitude. We call that Metropolis.

Started this piece as a rule based generative art. Simply the algorithm takes a rectangle and throws 2 random points inside it within defined x and y distances. Then using those 2 points, algorithm draws another rectangle and assigns letters to the corners of rectangle "A,B,C,D" starting from top left corner in clockwise direction. Then it starts to draw cells from inner rectangle's corner A to parent's corner A and goes on. Once 4 cells are created, it creates 4 more cells in between other cells, thus dividing a rectangle into 9 pieces. This is where "IX" comes from. Depending on the cell properties; algorithm assigns circles, triangles, lines and points to cells creating a city scape when certain parameters are given to the division algorithm.

There are 18 possible outcomes:
"Hazy Day" 13% probability (half of this style will come with slightly more color transition)
"Hazy Night" 10% probability
"Crystal Day" 11% probability
"Crystal Night" 5% probability
"Mondrian Day"  3% probability
"Mondrian Night" 3% probability
"Bauhaus Day" 3% probability
"Bauhaus Night" 3% probability
"1 Chroma Day" 4% probability (Multiple values of a single hue on a monochrome gradient)
"Mondrian Crystal Day" 3% probability
"Mondrian Crystal Night" 3% probability
"Monochrome Day" 3% probability 
"Monochrome Night" 4% probability 
"Vibrant Day" 12% probability
"Vibrant Night" 9% probability
"Rainbow Day' 5% probability
"Rainbow Night' 3% probability
"Chaotic Day"   3% probability (which takes pretty random parameters and 25% of this outcome has probability of creating very first coloring style of the project, see console for the hidden feature)




Press "1" to download 1000px height PNG
Press "2" to download 2000px height PNG
Press "3" to download 3000px height PNG
Press "4" to download 4000px height PNG
Press "5" to download 5000px height PNG
Press "6" to download 6000px height PNG
Press "7" to download 7000px height PNG
Press "8" to download 8000px height PNG
Press "9" to download 12000px height PNG
Press "m' to download 900x1600px PNG for mobile wallpaper

Use CTRL+SHIFT+C or CMD+SHIFT+C to open console for hidden features

Created from scratch with p5.js 
Murat Atimtay 2022 | @atimtay | www.muratatimtay.com

metadata.name: Galactica #97
metadata.description:
Galactica shows us the landscapes of a distant exoplanetary system made up of 10 planets.
Standing on one of these planets with its particular geomorphology, we may see faraway galaxies, natural satellites and/or another planet in the sky.

The combination of the various features can give life to up to 415,000 different versions, taking into account the differences not related to features the versions rise to about 12 billion.

Press "s" to get a 2000x2000 pixels jpg.

Generative artwork by Gandhiavelli, @gandhiavelli. Made with p5js in 2022.
License: CC BY-NC-ND 4.0
